## Executive Summary

Ireland’s Department of Foreign Affairs is a mid-level humanitarian
donor, providing an average annual funding around \$7.7 million, with
notable variability in amounts, regions, and recipient countries. Its
funding portfolio is diversified geographically, expanding from 6 to
nearly 9 countries supported between 2022 and 2025, with a strong focus
on global and Eastern regions. Approximately 25% of its funding is
earmarked, reflecting a balance between targeted and flexible support.
Contributions tend to be fewer in number but moderately sized, averaging
\$2.3 million per transaction. For fundraisers, aligning proposals with
Ireland’s shifting regional priorities and earmarking preferences, while
emphasizing adaptable programming, can enhance fundraising success.

## Volatility

This chart presents the funding trend from the Ireland Department of
